OriginalDataURL points here : https://doi.pangaea.de/10.1594/PANGAEA.737217?format=html#download which is from Leduc et al 2010a, https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0277379110000065, but it looks like the data are an amalgamation of Fig 3C and 3F data from Leduc et al 2010b, https://agupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1029/2010GL044353, datasets: https://doi.pangaea.de/10.1594/PANGAEA.808645 (1938-1999), and https://doi.pangaea.de/10.1594/PANGAEA.776883 (<=24-1937 CE).  But the data together span 35-1977CE.  And over 750-1950 they have r=1.00. Cannot find this data in Leduc et al (2010), http://www.guillaume-leduc.com/public/xls/Leduc2010GRL.xls, cores GeoB8331-MUC and GeoB8332-MUC (both: 1938-1999CE common timescale), GeoB8331-GC (23-1938CE).  Cannot easily find this data from Leduc et al (2010a); none of the listed records and data URLs span this time frame either.  Accept record 2 (35-1977) as some composite, with large uncertainty as to provenance and original datasets.  Use with caution until resolved.
